WHO EPIDEMIOLOGICAL BULLETIN SUMMARY FOR PERIOD 26 FEBRUARY TO 1 MARCH 1996
EBOLA HAEMORRHAGIC FEVER:
GABON:
AS AT 27 FEBRUARY A TOTAL OF 24 CASES WITH 17 DEATHS HAVE BEEN REPORTED IN
THE OUTBREAK IN THE VILLAGE OF MAYIBOUT II IN THE NORTH OF GABON. CONTROL
MEASURES INSTITUTED BY THE MINISTRY OF HEALTH AND THE INTERNATIONAL MEDICAL
TEAM APPEAR TO BE CONTAINING FURTHER SPREAD OF THE DISEASE ALTHOUGH SOME
SPORADIC SECONDARY CASES ARE EXPECTED. WHO DOES NOT RECOMMEND ANY TRAVEL
RESTRICTION TO OR WITHIN GABON.
CEREBROSPINAL MENINGITIS:
NIGERIA:
OUTBREAKS OF MENINGITIS HAVE BEEN REPORTED IN AT LEAST 11 STATES IN THE
NORTHERN PART OF THE COUNTRY AND A TOTAL OF 8423 CASES WITH 1181 DEATHS WERE
RECORDED AS AT 29 FEBRUARY. THE HIGHEST NUMBER OF CASES OCCURRED IN BAUCHI,
KADUNA, KATSINA AND KANO STATES. THE MINISTRY OF HEALTH HAS SENT FIVE
INVESTIGATION TEAMS TO THE AFFECTED AREAS. WHO, UNICEF, MSF EXPERTS HAVE
JOINED THESE TEAMS TO ASSIST IN THE CONTROL OPERATIONS.
CHOLERA:
NIGERIA:
OUTBREAKS OF CHOLERA HAVE RECENTLY BEEN REPORTED IN KANO, KWARA, ONDO AND
OYO STATES AND A TOTAL OF 1487 CASES WITH 99 DEATHS WERE RECORDED AS AT 29
FEBRUARY. THE HIGHEST NUMBER OF CASES OCCURRED IN KANO STATE.


